1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,280
<i>Mr. Yai got me drunk</i>
<i>and forced himself on me.</i>

2
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,440
<i>You bastard!</i>

3
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,560
You have a wife,
but you're still sleeping around!

4
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:33,680
Pin. I've been coming back
because I missed you.

5
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:37,360
Add this in, and tell Pin

6
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,680
to serve the food to Yai.

7
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,840
- Madam.
- I've never feared Madam Krongsuk.

8
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:43,640
But your mom is a serious problem.

9
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,400
<i>I'll send her to live somewhere else.</i>

10
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,600
Where is she?

11
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,760
Is she sneaking around being obscene?

12
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:10,160
All men are bastards.

13
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,440
There's not a single good one.

14
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:19,600
What now?! Why are you following me again?

15
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,920
- Give it back.
- No.

16
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:26,120
Why didn't you tell me
that the customer harassed you first?

17
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,680
Are you mute or something?

18
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,920
You were deaf.

19
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,720
That's why you didn't hear what I said.

20
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:35,920
My voice has been
falling on deaf ears all along.

21
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,920
- Give it back.
- No.

22
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,160
- I'm throwing it away.
- Give it back.

23
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,960
You yelled at me
even though I wasn't wrong.

24
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,840
Tatsanee, I can't breathe.

25
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,560
Let go of me.

26
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,280
There are a lot more animals now.

27
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:14,000
Mr. Paisal once said
that you love animals.

28
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:18,360
He seemed so happy to see these animals.

29
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,000
But unfortunately,

30
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:24,840
during the time when he was ill,
he couldn't take care of the farm.

31
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,800
So,

32
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,240
was my dad's condition very serious?

33
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:33,200
<i>Add five drops to his food daily.</i>

34
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:37,120
<i>Within a month,</i>
<i>he'll lose the ability to speak and walk.</i>

35
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,160
<i>He'll soon suffer heart failure.</i>

36
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,960
<i>No matter how skilled the doctor is,</i>
<i>they won't be able to detect poison.</i>

37
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,520
Mom.

38
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,200
Are you cooking for Madam?

39
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,920
No. Actually, I made it for you and…

40
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,480
your husband.

41
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,920
I realized I had gone too far yesterday.

42
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,320
So I didn't feel very good about it.

43
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,640
Mr. Yai won't hold anything against you.

44
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,360
And from now on, I'll handle

45
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:13,200
your daily meals myself.

46
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,560
Mr. Yai loves rad na.

47
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,440
If he knows it's your cooking,

48
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:23,960
he'll probably eat it all.

49
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,360
I did it for my daughter…

50
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,240
I did it for Madam…

51
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:44,840
Yai is evil. I didn't do anything wrong.

52
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:48,160
I did the right thing.

53
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,000
Look at you, Un.

54
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:55,120
Get a grip.

55
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,520
If you can't control yourself,
I'll get dragged down with you.

56
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,040
So,

57
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,920
did you make sure Yai ate it?

58
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:07,080
I don't know.
I didn't dare to look, Madam.

59
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,280
Madam.

60
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,000
Mr. Yai… Mr. Yai will just

61
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,160
be unable to speak and then

62
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:17,360
gradually stop breathing, right?

63
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,800
It won't be painful, right, Madam?

64
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,080
Keep your voice down.

65
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,440
Do you want someone to hear you?

66
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:27,040
Madam… I can't do it.

67
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,200
No more. I'm afraid.
I don't want to do it anymore.

68
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,240
Listen, Un.

69
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,640
I know.

70
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,640
I know how you feel.

71
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,320
Here's what we'll do.

72
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,560
I'll add the medicine in myself

73
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:47,200
so that if I get caught,
you won't have to worry.

74
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,640
I'll just die alone.

75
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,880
No, Madam.

76
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:59,640
I'll do it myself. I can do it.

77
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:06,920
Who's there?

78
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,360
Madam. Madam.

79
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,200
Did anyone hear us?

80
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:03,080
No. The pot might have fallen by itself.

81
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,160
Let's go back inside.

82
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,039
Mr. Yai.

83
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,400
Mr. Yai.

84
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,640
Oh, where's Madam Pin?

85
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,560
She went to give her salary to Aunt Un.

86
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,920
And she said that
you can go ahead and eat.

87
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,560
No need to wait for her.

88
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,520
Mr. Yai, don't eat yet.

89
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,200
Please wait for me.

90
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,880
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, don't eat…

91
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,960
Your mom must have felt so guilty that

92
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,960
she made me rad na to make me feel better.

93
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,560
Did you eat it all, Mr. Yai?

94
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,400
Well, of course.

95
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,960
Noi said Aunt Un made it,
so I ate every single bit.

96
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,240
You need to go to the bathroom
and throw up right now.

97
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,600
What's with you, Pin?

98
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,760
Why should I throw up something good?

99
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:25,240
- Well, I forgot to tell Noi that…
- What?

100
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,440
…there was a cockroach in it.

101
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,680
Oh, really?

102
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:35,440
And she said that
you can go ahead and eat.

103
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,880
No need to wait for her.

104
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,560
Oh?

105
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,720
That's Pin's seafood rad na.

106
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,560
Yours is the pork rad na.

107
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,560
Oh?

108
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,440
Well…

109
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,560
I was so hungry, I didn't even notice
which one had pork,

110
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,960
so I just ate your seafood rad na.

111
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:17,160
And it was delicious, so I ate it all.

112
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,400
I'm sorry. If you don't want pork,

113
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,360
I can order any delivery you want.

114
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,520
Come on, sit down.

115
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,680
What happened? Who did this?

116
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,120
Was it Nee or Madam?

117
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:38,600
No, Mr. Yai. Well…

118
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,960
I fell off my bike.

119
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,120
Where's the bike?

120
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,920
I'm going to tear it to pieces.

121
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,720
How dare it hurt my wife!

122
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,680
Are you thinking straight, Mr. Yai?

123
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,280
You're even picking on a bicycle?

124
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,800
I'm still upset with you.

125
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,520
How can I make you feel better?

126
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,000
Let me kiss your cheek.

127
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,200
Ms. Nee?

128
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,080
What happened to her?

129
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,440
No… No one loves me…

130
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:26,160
It seems like you've been spending
a lot of time with Tatsanee lately.

131
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,920
Well,

132
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,560
didn't you order me
to keep an eye on these people?

133
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,240
So I had to follow them around.

134
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:36,760
- Doing as I asked, huh?
- Yeah.

135
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:40,000
And I asked you for my dad's
medical records. What's the progress?

136
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,480
It's difficult, man.

137
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:44,680
It's been decades,
so it's bound to be a bit slow.

138
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:52,160
But fortunately,
my dad's old friend works at the hospital.

139
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,560
But from what I've seen,

140
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:59,000
your dad probably had
common heart failure.

141
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,560
What seems off to you?

142
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:06,600
Win said Dad could barely walk

143
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,760
due to muscle weakness
before the heart failure.

144
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:11,360
But his medical checkup records

145
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:13,520
show nothing but mild hypertension.

146
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,240
They don't show any diseases.

147
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,480
Do you think

148
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,280
someone was responsible
for your dad's death?

149
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,600
I don't think that's the case.

150
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:28,560
High blood pressure
can lead to a heart attack, you know.

151
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,280
- Noi.
- Yes?

152
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:48,840
I've told you not to let the madam
do the housework, haven't I?

153
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:52,040
Oh, already I told Pin, but she…

154
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,160
Don't be upset before the meal.

155
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:55,880
Have a seat.

156
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:05,080
I wanted to do it myself.

157
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,480
You're not a maid anymore, Pin.

158
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:13,160
Well, I want to take care of you myself.

159
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,920
From now on,

160
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,920
you must only eat food prepared by me.

161
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,760
Don't eat anywhere else.

162
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,960
Are you afraid I'll get COVID?

163
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:30,120
The food I prepare
is the cleanest and the safest.

164
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,440
Can you promise me that?

165
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:39,600
Are you worried about me, afraid I'll die,

166
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,000
or are you just trying to act like my mom?

167
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,840
Don't talk about death.

168
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,000
I won't ever let you die.

169
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,200
Mr. Yai, Noi is watching us.

170
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,320
Ever had a fork stuck in your eye?

171
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,160
My eye?

172
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,040
As you can see, it's perfectly fine.

173
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:23,800
Hey.

174
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,320
I'm sorry.

175
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,480
Mr. Yai.

176
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:40,040
Sit and eat properly.

177
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,560
I'm hungry.

178
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,280
Mr. Yai.

179
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,400
Pick up your pace, Na.

180
00:16:58,480 --> 00:16:59,880
They're waiting for us.

181
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,440
Which side of the family is it?

182
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,960
What are they doing here?

183
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:11,319
Come. Now is an auspicious time
to register your marriage.

184
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,520
Come on.

185
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,240
But…

186
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,720
it's not even the engagement day yet.

187
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,640
This is the auspicious day
for registration.

188
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:25,560
The monk recommended
that you register it before the ceremony,

189
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:29,120
so your fates would be bound together.

190
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,080
Alright?

191
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:31,800
Come on.

192
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,600
Yeah, right there.

193
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:37,240
- Take a seat, Na.
- Take a seat, dear.

194
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,640
You're back?

195
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,080
Are you tired?

196
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,600
I'm so exhausted, I can barely stand.

197
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,000
My legs are completely weak.

198
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:06,400
I was just worried.

199
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,720
I was afraid
Pin wouldn't be able to hold you.

200
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,320
Let me get a cool cloth to wipe your face.

201
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,280
Got a little more energy now.

202
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:23,720
Let's go.

203
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,720
The baby's coming for sure.

204
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,120
Mr. Yai, please don't eat yet.

205
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,960
I've already made lunch for Mr. Yai.

206
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,440
You don't have to bother, Mom.

207
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,600
- Noi, get me the plate.
- Yes?

208
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,840
- Now.
- Yes.

209
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:04,680
Put this away.

210
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:10,120
I made spaghetti
with spicy seafood for you.

211
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:12,400
Last time, Noi said that

212
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:15,720
you told her the seafood rad na
was delicious.

213
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,120
For me?

214
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,320
Yes.

215
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:29,200
I went too far with you the other day,

216
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:31,320
so I wanted to apologize.

217
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:39,160
I'm a blunt person, so I can be a little
inconsiderate of others sometimes.

218
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:43,800
Please consider this dish my apology.

219
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:52,680
Alright. Given with heart,
received with heart, Aunt Un.

220
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,480
Wait.

221
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,360
Hey, don't!

222
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,360
You can't eat it.

223
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,760
You… You're allergic to mussels.

224
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,600
They give you diarrhea.

225
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:43,920
Have you forgotten already?

226
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,160
I haven't been allergic for a long time.

227
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:48,720
It's Mr. Yai who's allergic.

228
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:53,880
Oh, my.

229
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:57,800
Are you allergic to mussels too?

230
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:01,120
I'm so sorry.

231
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,840
You were acting strange today, Pin.

232
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,480
What did I do?

233
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:23,880
Why did you have to eat the food
your mom made for me?

234
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:26,280
Well, you're allergic to mussels.

235
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:28,440
If I didn't eat it for you,
Mom would have been upset again.

236
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:30,200
I'm not allergic to mussels.

237
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:33,720
Oh?

238
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,920
When we were little,
I remember you had diarrhea

239
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,000
and needed an IV to recover.

240
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,160
Maybe I misremembered.

241
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,400
<i>Suddenly,</i>
<i>Mr. Paisal became easily fatigued,</i>

242
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:12,640
his limbs felt weak, and he was confined
to his bed in the main house.

243
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:16,200
Madam said he had heart disease
and couldn't do any hard work.

244
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:18,160
We never visited him

245
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,760
because Madam forbade anyone to…

246
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:24,520
until he passed away at the hospital.

247
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:41,680
<i>Aunt Un is working as usual.</i>

248
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,440
<i>She goes to the market in the morning</i>

249
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:46,080
<i>then returns to serve Madam Krongsuk.</i>

250
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,040
<i>Then she goes to the main house</i>
<i>to cook for you.</i>

251
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,720
<i>In the afternoon, she takes a nap.</i>

252
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,280
<i>And in the evening, she cooks again.</i>

253
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,400
<i>That's her daily life.</i>

254
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,880
She seems to be acting
particularly nice to me lately.

255
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,960
Sure. She's probably thinking
of getting money from your wife.

256
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:07,680
Be careful,
or she'll drain your wallet dry.

257
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:10,600
Hey, don't try to break up my family.

258
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:14,600
Hey. Didn't you say
you gave up being single

259
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:16,280
because you wanted to test if Puny Pin

260
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:18,640
had joined Madam's scammer gang?

261
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:21,720
Yeah, of course.

262
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,400
I tested her, and she hasn't.

263
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,840
Then what's next?

264
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:25,760
Well…

265
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:28,120
How can I break up
right after getting married?

266
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:30,600
I have to wait for the right moment,
deploy some tactics.

267
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,800
Tactics?

268
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,920
You've been using tactics for a long time.

269
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:38,680
Here.

270
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,080
Here you go.

271
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:44,760
Remember, the one I made for you

272
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,000
doesn't have chilis.

273
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:50,720
And

274
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:54,440
did Mr. Yai finish the fish porridge
this morning?

275
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,080
He did.

276
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:02,160
And the spaghetti I made for him,

277
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,920
did he eat it?

278
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,240
Yes, he did.

279
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,160
Good.

280
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:14,560
Then I'll get back to helping Madam.

281
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:17,080
Hey, don't forget.

282
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:19,000
Yours is the not spicy one.

283
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:08,080
Have you helped a man get dressed before?

284
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,240
You seem so good at it.

285
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:10,840
Yes.

286
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:14,520
Who was it? Na?

287
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:18,120
Do you want me to say yes?

288
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:25,920
Mr. Yai, I was just joking.

289
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,840
Are you really going to sulk over this?

290
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:36,080
You haven't changed a bit.

291
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,000
I was talking about Uncle Paisal.

292
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:43,480
When he was sick and bedridden,

293
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:44,840
I was his caregiver.

294
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:48,440
He couldn't speak or move,

295
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:50,280
so I had to dress him.

296
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,400
Fine.

297
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,400
I'll stop talking then.

298
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:04,360
You tease me and then walk away, Puny Pin?

299
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,520
No, I'm not teasing you.

300
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,880
I've been sleeping on the sofa
for many nights,

301
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,000
hoping you'd feel sorry for me.

302
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,560
But you're so heartless.

303
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,280
I can't stand it anymore, Pin.

304
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,880
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, please don't.

305
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,960
Mr. Yai. Please stop.

306
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:09,360
I beg you.

307
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:11,600
Please, Mr. Yai.

308
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:25,680
I forgot you married me just to spite Na.

309
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:30,240
I just need some time.

310
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:33,640
I'm not ready right now.

311
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:45,920
I thought I understood you.

312
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,880
But no.

313
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,080
I never understood you at all.

314
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,760
Sir, you can't put that up here.

315
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:29,520
We have to wait for the Secretary
to return, or I'll call the police.

316
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:42,360
Miss, a court official is
about to post a notice on the property.

317
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:44,560
Get out of here.

318
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:46,400
Don't come and post anything here.

319
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:48,000
Give it here.

320
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:49,160
No, ma'am.

321
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:51,280
This is a court order
to seize the property.

322
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:54,000
Anyone who tears it up
will be punished by the law.

323
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,120
IN THE NAME OF HIS MAJESTY THE KING
CIVIL COURT

324
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:16,320
Is this why you pressured me
to sign the marriage certificate?

325
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:19,120
It's just a liquidity issue.

326
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:21,640
We're just a bit short on cash,
like many people are.

327
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,800
It's no big deal.

328
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:27,480
A seizure warrant was posted at the gate,

329
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:29,440
and you still say it's no big deal?

330
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:32,760
Well, you have a lot of money,
so what's there to be afraid of?

331
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:35,920
Once we're married,
you'll have to help me anyway.

332
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,560
Or will you not help me?

333
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:41,360
Turns out you only decided to marry me

334
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,320
because you wanted me
to help you pay off your debts.

335
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:48,640
I was under the impression

336
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,600
that you loved me.

337
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:54,520
Or do you not really love my daughter?

338
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,160
Is that why you can't help?

339
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,400
Asking for help

340
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,560
and outright deception

341
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,240
are two different things, ma'am.

342
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,520
Na. Na.

343
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:07,320
Mom.

344
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:08,840
Mom.

345
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,320
Mom. What's wrong? Mom.

346
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:31,200
Here.

347
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:33,600
Madam, that's enough.

348
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:36,440
If we add too much,
he could have a sudden heart attack,

349
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:37,760
and we could get caught.

350
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:40,880
I want to see him die as soon as possible.

351
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:44,360
- Madam, that's enough. Please.
- Hey.

352
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,160
Hey, Na needs money for the dowry.

353
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,480
I can't wait any longer.

354
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:49,760
If you're too scared to do it,
I'll do it myself.

355
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:02,560
You have to come back
to have lunch with me, okay?

356
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,040
Don't touch anyone else's cooking.

357
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,800
I'll think about it.

358
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,760
Maybe I'll eat with Pan.

359
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,520
Just you wait.

360
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,760
MR. TATSANA

361
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,320
Mr. Na?

362
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:48,800
<i>Pin. I wanna die.</i>

363
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:53,000
<i>I wanna die, Pin. I wanna die!</i>

364
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:23,560
Mr. Na.

365
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:25,880
Mr. Na.

366
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:29,680
Mr. Na! Mr. Na!

367
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,120
Mr. Na.

368
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,120
Why are you so drunk?

369
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,400
Mr. Na. Mr. Na.

370
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,000
Take care of the rest for me, alright?

371
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:55,240
Check for pests too.

372
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:57,160
- Yes.
- See if they're eating our plants.

373
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,400
- Go on.
- Yes, Uncle Win.

374
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,040
Uncle Win.

375
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:06,200
I just saw Mr. Yai around here.

376
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:07,600
Where did he go?

377
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:10,200
I brought the pet food check
for him to sign.

378
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:13,640
Oh, Nittaya told us
that a guest at the resort

379
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:15,600
went up the mountain and had an accident.

380
00:33:15,680 --> 00:33:18,080
We called the rescue team,
but Mr. Yai also wanted to go see.

381
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:19,880
I just saw the news.

382
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:21,440
They said a storm is coming.

383
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,440
I wanna die, Pin.

384
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,760
I can't see any way out.

385
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,480
My life is completely ruined.

386
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:39,920
It's over.

387
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,960
There's no way forward.

388
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:45,480
In front of me…

389
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,280
is only a cliff.

390
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:59,120
Every problem has a solution.

391
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:02,840
You should go back
and tell the truth to Madam.

392
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:11,840
If Auntie finds out that
On's family is bankrupt,

393
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:15,040
she'll definitely kill me, Pin.

394
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,639
She's going to kill me!

395
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:19,400
If you run away from Ms. On like this,

396
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:21,120
she would probably be upset too.

397
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:24,840
But she lied to me.

398
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,120
She isn't as sincere as you, Pin.

399
00:34:27,199 --> 00:34:29,480
Pin. Pin.

400
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:32,560
I was so blind.

401
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:34,639
I chose the wrong woman.

402
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,719
Let's give us another chance.

403
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,280
Please, Pin. Please.

404
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:39,920
- Mr. Na.
- Pin.

405
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:40,960
Mr. Na, stop.

406
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:43,080
Mr. Na, let me go. Let go of me.

407
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:44,360
Don't you love me anymore?

408
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,840
Let go. Let go.

409
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:48,639
Stop!

410
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:57,280
So why did you come
all this way to see me,

411
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:59,360
if not because you still love me?!

412
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,520
You treated death like a joke

413
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,960
and tricked me into coming here.

414
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:07,360
Pin. I…

415
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:10,040
I'm going to divorce On.

416
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,800
You just need to divorce Mr. Yai.

417
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:17,160
And then we can get back together. Okay?

418
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,600
I don't love you anymore.

419
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:22,640
You're lying.

420
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:27,520
You're just still upset
with me, aren't you?

421
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:29,040
Right?

422
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,160
What is it, Noi?

423
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,840
Mr. Yai is stuck on the mountain.

424
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,080
The rain has blocked all the roads,

425
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:41,920
<i>and we can't get in touch with him.</i>

426
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,040
Hey, hey. Pin.

427
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,120
Please don't go.

428
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:51,960
I was drunk earlier and lost myself.

429
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,200
Stay with me, Pin.

430
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:55,360
- Mr. Na.
- I've lost all hope in life.

431
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:57,080
Please stay with me.

432
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,680
I really need your encouragement. Please.

433
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:01,520
- Please, Pin.
- Mr. Na.

434
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:06,280
- Pin! Pin! But…
- Mr. Na.

435
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:07,920
But I never loved On.

436
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,240
Mr. Na, let go of me.

437
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:10,760
I never loved On.

438
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,920
- Pin. Pin.
- Let me go.

439
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:17,520
I love Mr. Yai.

440
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:21,040
Do you hear me?

441
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:24,200
Stay away from me.

442
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,200
Pin. Pin!

443
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,400
Yai…

444
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:45,880
Yai!

445
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:24,440
Mr. Yai. Please be okay.

446
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,080
Pin.

447
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:35,800
Noi, is there any word yet on Mr. Yai?

448
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:38,280
<i>Not yet. Are you close to the farm?</i>

449
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:40,920
I'm almost at the national park.

450
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,920
<i>Huh? Are you going up the mountain?</i>

451
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:46,400
<i>No, Pin. Pin!</i>

452
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,160
Mr. Yai.

453
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:00,840
Mr. Yai!

454
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:02,920
Mr. Yai!

455
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:05,960
Mr. Yai.

456
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:09,240
- Mr. Yai.
- Pin?

457
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:16,000
There's no signal.

458
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:21,160
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, are you hurt?

459
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,600
Can you get up?

460
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:32,280
I'll help you get into the car.

461
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:34,000
Please hang in there.

462
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:37,160
Why are you here, Pin?

463
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:39,680
I was worried about you.

464
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:43,240
Go now.

465
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:45,960
The water is rushing
down the mountain like crazy.

466
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:50,880
How could I leave you behind?

467
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:54,360
Leave the area now.

468
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:57,360
You aren't strong enough
to carry me, Pin. Go.

469
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,440
Pin! How's Yai?! Please hurry up!

470
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:07,080
Mr. Yai rescued the guest
from the mountain

471
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,720
and had me take them to the hospital.

472
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:13,560
I never thought that an accident
would happen to Mr. Yai.

473
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:19,200
Hey, Doctor.

474
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:20,800
How is he doing?

475
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:23,680
There are a few small wounds
on his head, nothing serious.

476
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:26,680
But he has a high fever from
being out in the rain for a long time.

477
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:30,080
Once his fever goes down,
I think you should take him

478
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:32,760
for a brain scan
to check for other symptoms.

479
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:38,160
Thank you, man, for coming all this way.

480
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:39,600
Let me give you a ride.

481
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:18,920
Mr. Yai, don't go…

482
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:26,440
Mr. Yai?

483
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,760
You wouldn't wake up.

484
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:36,320
I was so scared.

485
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:40,560
What did you dream about, Pin?

486
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:54,720
I dreamt that we had to part ways.

487
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,520
I will never let you go.

488
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:14,200
Is it because I saved your life?

489
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:18,160
I don't know when it happened.

490
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:26,040
I don't know where it started.

491
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:31,640
It's been a while since it happened.

492
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:38,000
Maybe it was

493
00:42:38,880 --> 00:42:40,320
when my dad scolded me

494
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,480
and you comforted me after it.

495
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:48,080
Or maybe it was the day
you shared your food with me.

496
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,960
Or was it

497
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:59,880
when I often secretly came
to see you at the farm?

498
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,280
I'm not sure.

499
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:08,960
<i>I was already in college back then,</i>

500
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:11,200
<i>and you weren't living here.</i>

501
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:14,720
<i>Or have you been back to the farm?</i>

502
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,680
<i>Uh… I…</i>

503
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:20,880
I was here to see Tuem.

504
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:22,000
I was worried about him.

505
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:25,960
I've been coming back…

506
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,760
because I missed you.

507
00:43:45,280 --> 00:43:47,040
You're crying again, Pin.

508
00:43:58,000 --> 00:44:00,080
I have something to tell you too.

509
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:07,960
I no longer have feelings for Mr. Tatsana.

510
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:17,680
I don't believe you.

511
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:20,360
You're lying to me.

512
00:44:47,240 --> 00:44:50,320
Pin rushed all the way
to reignite an old flame

513
00:44:50,400 --> 00:44:52,600
with Na at his hotel room.

514
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,320
Don't make me ask again!

515
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:55,200
<i>We love each other.</i>

516
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:58,040
Pin wants a divorce,
but she's afraid you'd hurt her.

517
00:44:58,120 --> 00:44:59,240
I'll search Pinanong's room.

518
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:00,840
No need to search.

519
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:03,200
The medicine is in the bedroom,
dressing table drawer.

520
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:06,600
Mom's heart condition is acting up!

521
00:45:48,560 --> 00:45:50,800
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
